    <h1>Validation Utils Changelog</h1>

    <div class="changelog-entry">
      <h3>2025-04-11</h3>
      <p class="date">April 11, 2025</p>
      <p>
        <span class="change-type fix">FIX:</span>
        Replaced global <code>isNaN()</code> with more robust <code>Number.isNaN()</code> in the
        <code>isValidISODate()</code> function. This change improves type safety and prevents
        unexpected behavior when validating date strings.
      </p>
      <p><strong>File:</strong> validation.utils.ts</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Reason:</strong> The global <code>isNaN()</code> function attempts to convert its
        argument to a number before checking, which can lead to unexpected results with non-numeric
        inputs. <code>Number.isNaN()</code> is more strict and only returns true if the value is
        exactly the <code>NaN</code> value, providing more predictable behavior.
      </p>
    </div>
